The paper deals with unsupervised near-duplicate detection in images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction also falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of false positives, which is a concern in computer security (cs.CR).
